dusklar</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Only problem I see in that "just give the cleric enough gmes" idea is what you touched on Josie, that alot of camps don't drop alot of gems.. therefore the cleric gets to freely supply dots out of his pocket.. I guarantee that I have done that many more times than received an overpayment in sebilis.  Saying gems should not be a source of income is like saying " ok I will symbol you only in places that drop gems.".. not too many tanks would like that answer.. <P>Anyone that plays a cleric that gives free rezzes, and purchases his spells, armor, and other components realizes that we normally lead a pretty low income life... I think the most plat I have ever had in EQ is around 6k.  I would shudder to think how much symboling I have spent.. easily 30K. if not more<P>Dusklar 60th Cleric</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey Bab0linskey</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's always kind of intresting to see the difference in server ettiquette.<P>For the 50 plus game pp and gems aren't going to make you rich by any standards (unless OS is such a gem heaven that it is possible (I xp'ed in OS 3 times)).  It's selling loot that makes real plat... <P>Beyond that, even if I did regulary get more then cost, I would argue that I do deserve it.  It's me that's gotta get the port (there goes a gem), get the charisma buff and get the gems.<P>I'd also argue for roleplay reasons, that as the priest of the group I collect the churchs cut.  Those poor oprhan's of Rivervale are always needing a roof patched, or another bowl of stew.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wisecleric</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Often a group will automatically hand you gems, no questions asked. <P>At what point do you say, "I got enough for now, you keep it."? <P>I know a few times i just kept my mouth shut besides the obligatory "Thanks so-and-so for the <insert gem>." <P>I look at it like the groups where 3-4 people never want to loot and just leave corpses laying around. If they don't want to loot and let me get rich, who am i to say no? <P>I think a lot of the instances where clerics "clean up" are like this. Meaning the people in the group dont care about cash and don't mind if the person actually having to spend cash gets the lion's share. <P>I think its our responsibility to not instantly think ever group feel do the same however. <P>Generally i would do the 3 gem/trinket item then we all rotate. Most often one or 2 melees in the group would toss me their loot gems anyways, meaning i would come out on top at the end. <P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Quotison</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">First... I don't think any class, including clerics is "greedy". There are members of all classes that are greedy, including greedy clerics.<P>I don't know what the situation is like with symbol costs since I'm only level 36.... in my opinion, after the cleric gets enough gems, cash, etc to cover symboling, all the other loot should be equally spread out, to everyone, including the cleric. If a cleric uses 150pp in symbols, he should not get 600pp, with everyone else getting only 100pp.<P>In places without good loot... then shouldn't everyone contribute to the symbol costs then? <P>Just observations by someone who has never experienced any of this before  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"> No matter what the method, the ultimate goal should be that everyone split the costs, and everyone split the loot, evenly.<P>Quotison<BR>Level 36 Cleric<BR>Still Using 1pp reagents.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In sebilis, I share. I expect all gems (non-JC of course) to be handed to me, and every 6th gem, I hand 1 to every person in the group.<P>Melees (who usualy loot and thus get the PPs too) get the Fire Opals and other low end gems. Enchanters and myself get the Sapphire Necklaces, Ruby Crowns and other high end gems. (Unless the enchanter specifically askes for the Fire Opals to make Rings out of)<P>This way, everyone is happy, and I still get the lion's share of the cash drops, ensuring myself that next time I am someplace where the cash drops are low, I wont run out of peridots.<P>Even doing this, I can STILL bank 1k+ on a good night in Sebilis.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JaigeTZ</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Whenever I go to a zone with lots of money loots I take as many gems as I can. 90% of the time I am with guildmates anyways so its no problem.<P>------------------<BR><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=22928" TARGET=_blank>Jaige Paranoid</A></B><BR>58 Templar of Innoruuk<BR><A HREF="http://pub92.ezboard.com/bexordium22946" TARGET=_blank>Exordium</A><BR>Tallon Zek</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Nemean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Twinskey,<BR>OS IS a gem heaven.  They drop like water down there, and after a nights xping you can easily make 1500pp after covering your dot costs.  So within a week of getting all the gems, you can crack 10K.  Thats why some of the other classes are beginning to get a bit irate about clerics getting all the gems in OS.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ikdu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I only exp with friends, but i am 60. They give me all gems(including BD ect), and i buff them/raid with them all the time. I do make "alot" of money off gems. But I use alot of dots on guild raids so it all evens out. Clerics should get all gems even BD.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">canddari</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When i do XP grps (non guild) i always share.<BR>Some of you ppl i see post here is the reason for the greddy cleric talk.<BR>When my costs are coverd i alwys hand out the extras. Sometimes my grp tells me to keep the gems and i dont argue with them  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>Not only clerics need PP. Most loot is for melee so i guess this is why some clerics think they should get all gems. They seem to think that mages/wizzys/necros should solo for there pp needs cous cleric solo sucks, and that due to the fact of 49 lvls of poverty they deserve a big payoff in HS/OS.<P>First time i was in seb (think i was 52) i got all the gems, dident think mutch off it. After i sold and restockd i had made 1.2k ... i was like OMG and then it made me feel like i cheated my grp. So after that i make sure i share.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial"> <BLOCKQUOTE><font size="1" face="Verdana, Arial">quote:</font><HR>Originally posted by Ikdu:<BR><B>I only exp with friends, but i am 60. They give me all gems(including BD ect), and i buff them/raid with them all the time. I do make "alot" of money off gems. But I use alot of dots on guild raids so it all evens out. Clerics should get all gems even BD.</B><HR></BLOCKQUOTE><P>Please tell me you don't really believe this?? I mean, come on, EVERYONE has a need for resist gear, so EVERYONE should get a shot at Blue Diamonds and Diamonds. And the other rare type JC gems (Jacinths, Black Saphhires) should get group randomed or given to the enchanter who can actually MAKE something with them.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Sullah</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Here's my little story from last night...<P>   I zoned into Sebilis looking for a little killing action and formed a crypt group.  I was constantly being handed gems and after 5 gems I told the group "I have more than enough gems to last me the night, please loot up guys".  There were a few remarks such as "Wow, that's the first time I have ever heard that!" and "Are you sure?" "Glad to hear a cleric finally fesses up".  <P>   I have heard from other cleric friends that they make an average of 1-2K a night *profit* in gems when in Sebilis.  This is unfair, stupid and greedy.   Other group memebers need money too (especially monks who cannot carry coins)  I know several clerics who have 10-30K in the bank from these expeditions while I have a significant but lowly 3-5K usually.  The only reason they get away with it is because groups can't afford clerics to leave a group.  Well after a little while in Seb certain reputations will outweigh others when multiple clerics are LFG, guess who's gonna get the invite?  (Not the greedy cleric for sure)<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dannig</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">For me, I usually get the gems to cover the dots used, then tell the ML to alpha split the cash items from there on out.<BR>Most groups LOVE me for that  <IMG SRC="http://eqcleric.gameglow.com/ubb/smile.gif"><P>------------------<BR>Dannig   55 Cleric<BR>Dark Elf<BR>Member of The Commune <BR>Xegony<P>group01 "Dannig, heal yourself"<BR>you tell the group "Oh yeah  :) "</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Josiefuz</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">It's obvious the servers vary on this issue.  I don't want all the gems, I just want enough to cover my costs.  If I got all the gems in a seb group I'd make a killing!  I don't want to make a killing, I just want my fair share.  <P>Sol Ro uses the first 3 gems to the cleric.  I usually get in a group and stay there for 3 hours.  This means 1 gem per hour.  At level 54 that meant 18 symbols cast (200pp) for 150-300pp in gems (depending on if you got cheap fire opals or better gems).  In a weeks time of xping each nite I usually came out slightly ahead (less that 500pp ahead).<P>Once I got Symbol of Naltron my symbol costs dropped slightly because I can save a few dots in that same 3 hours.  Given the same scenario I net about 1k-1.5k per week over my dot costs.  Keep in mind it cost me 10k to buy that spell though, so I have almost broken even.<P>Fighting in those horrible zones where symbols are needed but gems don't drop, I pass along the cost to my group.  They either get cheaper symbols (Only naltron's mark, no Martzin) or they find another way to pay me back (more loots, a decent item, or they cough up the peridots themselves).  Just like I don't try to take more than my share from a group, I don't feel it's necessary to give more than my share either.  <P>The bottom line is that we each have a personal decision to make in this matter.  Even the clerics (us) don't agree what is correct.  What one cleric calls greed another cleric calls fair.  Even if we did all agree, what the clerics called fair, some other class would call greed.<P>Let's continue to discuss and share, but not point fingers at each other.  As always, our milage will vary.<P>-Fuz<BR>58 Templar, Sol Ro<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Entare</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Unfortunately, I have to agree with what most of the people had to say about clerics, expecially in OS.  My main is a level 60 magician, who hardly gets played outside of raids.<P>My cleric is only level 44, but since we only have 1 or 2 clerics that don't play that much, I often end up grouping with a lot of 56+ guildmates in Sebilis or Velks.<P>In a tipical evening at necropsis, JUST in gems you can expect around 1kpp an hour.<P>Let me clear something up:  Every group SHOULD pay clerics their components.  What every group shouldn't do is pay for the clerics rare spells and their raid expenses.  If you are grouping with only people in your guild, then by all means loot as much as you feel appropriate, since you will use that money when raiding with them, however, if you are in a group of people that you do not know, you cannot expect them to pay for the peridots that you use when raiding with other people.<P>Magicians hardly spend any money on pearls during day to day grouping, but if you are the only mage in a halls of testing raid you can easily go through 60+ pearls in one session.<P>If I spend money raiding, I just inform the raid leader of how much I spent, and usually I am at least reinbursed partially for the pearls.  I would consider it totally out of the line for me to ask a group of people I didn't know to fork over cash so that I can pay for pearls that I didn't use for them.<P>The money that you get from a group should be equal to a your expenses for the evening, plus a fair share of the rest of the money.  If you had horrible gem drops, lots of dispelling mobs and wipeouts, by all means get all of the gems, but if at the end of the day you can bank 1kpp after paying for your costs, and everyone else banks 100pp, then you are a disgrace to our class.<P>Clerics have it VERY easy with dropped post 50 spells, try being a shaman, or a necromancer.  The 59 pet spell is worth 100kpp on my server.  Does that mean that a necro is entitled to a higher share of the loot because his spells are more expensive?  Some cleric seem to think so.<P>To the cleric that said that he thinks he should get every gem, or the clerics that think that it is allright to bank 1kpp per session, you are A SHAME to your class, you are the ones that give us the reputation.<P>Now, to all those clerics that think stiffing the group is fine, just a question, how many tinker bags do you own?<P>End</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">JesterDK</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Plz guys only post if you know what youre talking about. I mean come on. A level 44 Cleric talking about dots spent ? Get Naltron first, use it for a while and see how you like it then.<P>I run through dots faster than i run through the food. Rarely reimbursed except for when hunting in Sebilis in Guard / NG or whatever its called on your server.<P>I think its a good suggestion to say 3 gems to cleric rest alpha. Nice system and is fair in most camps in Sebilis. But come on. We need to get reimbursed for all the dots we use in the camps in Velketors or in all the other camps were in. This argument will get beaten upon alot, cause "It cant be right i need to pay you for whatever camp you were in last night!". No, it cant. But tough luck, will you prefer if i just say, hey, i will only symbol you after i get paid ? In the middle of combat the warrior goes "Symbol faded" and you reply "well, geeze. Come over here with 11pp and then i will symbol you!" Face it. We get screwed if we dont act like asses some times. <P>I would surely wish that i could teach all the non-clerics out there a lesson. Would be nice if each and every cleric stayed away from camps other than in sebilis where the gems actually are found. Then they would be the ones with the problems and not us. I can almost hear it: <P>"a_stupid_warrior_01 tells you: We need a cleric for a camp in velketors and for some resses, would you consider coming plz?"<P>"You tell a_stupid_warrior_01: Too bad. You guys are the ones who dont want us to break even on gems. Get a necro to ress you and a druid to heal yass"<P>15 mins later....<P>"a_stupid_warrior_01: We had our 10th wipeout tonight, would you PLEASE come and help us. I lost a whole lot of xp and we allready bought peridots for you! And we have a gater standing by!"<P>"You tell a_stupid_warrior_01: Ok