 system, where guilds have to exp <I>together</I> in order to be able to finance their raids. I prefer the easy system.<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gimmel Greatheart</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">In my alliance of guilds we have an entry fee for planes raids, 50pp for clerics/chanters and 100pp for everyone else. All trinkets go to the alliance treasury which goes for reimbursement costs for non-fee raids (like epic raids). The trinkets for a single Hate raid can easily total 5k, which will fund peridots for several raids. It's not that tough, really, and I only lose money on peridots in exp groups, but that is more my fault than anything, since I rarely ask for reimbursment. For me at least, it would be disingenous to ask other people to fund my raids, since we fund them just fine. Taking the first few and alpha after that seems the easiest.</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
